title: Perfect Dark (Emulator with Keyboard and Mouse) playthrough -- Part 1
description: Apologies for the constant muting of my mic and sniffling and the crashing at the end. Other than all that shit, I'm enjoying this game a lot. I'm using 1964 with a mouse injector made specifically for Perfect Dark and Goldeneye. It's very easy to find and setup, and it works quite well. It makes the game easier though, since the framerate is mostly stable and mouse aim is easier than using a control stick; that's why I decided to play on Perfect Agent difficulty. Also the fact that you get more objectives is cool, I think. This makes me want to play Goldeneye, so I might just do that after I finish this game.
